meanings.definition: Not planned or rehearsed in advance
meanings.sent1: The unchoreographed dance performance was full of spontaneity.
meanings.sent2: The actors delivered an unchoreographed dialogue that felt natural.
meanings.sent3: The unchoreographed chaos on stage made the audience burst into laughter.
meanings.sent4: Her unchoreographed movements were like a wild dance of freedom.
meanings.sent5: The unchoreographed nature of the event left a lasting impression on everyone.

meanings.sent1: The unchoreographed movements of the protesters caught the police off guard.
meanings.sent2: The unchoreographed fight scene in the movie added realism to the action.
meanings.sent3: The unchoreographed traffic jam caused delays for hours.
meanings.sent4: His unchoreographed actions spoke louder than any planned speech.
meanings.sent5: The unchoreographed chaos of the city streets was both thrilling and unpredictable.
